Heat a large saucepan and fry the chorizo for 2-3 minutes.Add the garlic and cook for one minute. Add the cherry tomatoes, chickpeas and olives and cook for 2-3 minutes.In a separate frying pan, heat the olive oil, add the new potatoes and sauté until golden-brown on all sides. Add the sautéed potatoes to the tomato stew, then pour the mixture into an ovenproof dish.Preheat the grill to medium.Place the breadcrumbs and parsley into a small bowl and mix together. Sprinkle the breadcrumb mixture over the stew, then place under the grill and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until golden-brown on top. Serve in the dish.